                    <note xml:lang="en" type="description">In hagiography: Cyriacus was bishop of
                            <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/8">Amida</placeName> and came
                        from the monastery of Mar Zakka near <placeName
                            ref="http://syriaca.org/place/78">Edessa</placeName>. His church was
                        seized by the Chalcedonians, but he restored his churches under Khusro II.
                        He was the author of 30 ecclesiastical canons.</note>
